Subject: Penguicon Board Meeting
Description: You've done the convention, you've met the staff, and you've even socialized with the ConCom.  But what about those *other* Penguicon people?  Those shadowy figures that create the multi-year rules, have their fingers on the money, and cause a ConChair to mysteriously appear every year in a puff of penguin-scented smoke?  Ever wonder what the Penguicon Board of Directors does in their secret sanctum, and where they are taking Penguicon?  Come to the Board of Directors meeting and see!  Speakers include:Steve Gutterman, Randy Bradakis, Matt Arnold, Jer Lance,Amanda Long-Adams, Gini Judd, James Hice - Track: Penguicon  - Duration: 1 hour and 50 minutes

Subject: Everything and Anything with BeagleBone
Description: Explore the high-performance, low-power world with the tiny, affordable, open-source Beagles at Penguicon. Putting Android, Ubuntu and other Linux flavors at your fingertips.   Speakers include:Drew Fustini, James Hice - Track: DIY, Tech  - Duration: 1 hour and 50 minutes

Subject: The Continuing Penguicon Robot Build
Description: Come help design and build a robot during the convention. Donations may be accepted depending on the robot design. No skill necessary to help but prior experience would be useful. Useful skills include familiarity with micro-controllers, structural design, costume design, programming, graphic design, and logic!  Speakers include:James Hice, John D. Bell - Track: DIY, Tech  - Duration: 2 hours and 50 minutes
